{
  "info": {
    "name": "Notification Service",
    "description": "Local API collection for cosmicforge notification-service (port 8106).\n\nThe notification-service is the central service for all platform notifications (push, email, websocket, in_app). API base path: /api/v1/notifications.\n\nAuth modes:\n- Service endpoints (/send, /messages, /realtime/token, /devices): service-to-service HMAC (shared/go/serviceauth). The 'Service (HMAC)' folder signs requests automatically via a pre-request script using {{service_name}} / {{service_secret}}.\n- WebSocket (/ws): no HMAC; gated by a realtime token minted from /realtime/token (Postman cannot open ws:// — see the WebSocket request notes).\n\nApp-facing proxies (so apps never hold the HMAC secret):\n- Customer app -> customer-service /api/v1/customer/notifications (bearer, role=customer, service=customer).\n- Provider app -> driver-hauling-service /api/v1/hauling/provider/notifications (bearer, service=hauling).\nThe proxy services sign the downstream HMAC call on the app's behalf.\n\nMint dev bearer tokens for the proxy folders with: go run ./docs/devtoken -kind=customer (or -kind=provider -service=hauling). See docs/README.md.",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "Health",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "GET /health",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/health", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["health"] }
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "GET /ready",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
